SWRL rules

  • BeachAttractionRecommendation
  • CulturalEventRecommendation
  • GastronomicEventRecommendation
  • SeniorSportsEventRestriction
  • YouthDiscountEligibility

BeachAttractionRecommendationback to ToC or SWRL ToC

Recommends beach attractions to tourists who selected "Playa" (Beach) as their tourism type and are located in a city with beach attractions.

Tourist c(?t) , tourismType dp(?t,"Playa") , tourist is in city op(?t,?c) , city has attraction op(?c,?a) , attraction Beach c(?a) -> recomende attraction for tourist op(?t,?a)

CulturalEventRecommendationback to ToC or SWRL ToC

Recommends cultural events to tourists who are currently in a city and have selected "Cultural" as their tourism preference. If a city hosts a cultural event, it is suggested to those tourists.

Tourist c(?t) , tourismType dp(?t,"Cultural") , tourist is in city op(?t,?c) , city has event op(?c,?e) , event Cultural c(?e) -> recomende event for tourist op(?t,?e)

GastronomicEventRecommendationback to ToC or SWRL ToC

Recommends gastronomic events to tourists who prefer "Gastronmico" tourism and are located in a city where such events are held.

Tourist c(?t) , tourismType dp(?t,"Gastronmico") , tourist is in city op(?t,?c) , city has event op(?c,?e) , event Gastronomic c(?e) -> recomende event for tourist op(?t,?e)

SeniorSportsEventRestrictionback to ToC or SWRL ToC

Prevents the recommendation of sports events to tourists over the age of 59. This rule flags those events as denied for senior tourists currently staying in a city hosting sports-related events.

Tourist c(?t) , tourist_age dp(?t,?a) , greaterThan(?) , tourist is in city op(?t,?c) , city has event op(?c,?e) , event Sports c(?e) -> denegatedEvent op(?t,?e)

YouthDiscountEligibilityback to ToC or SWRL ToC

Grants a discount coupon to tourists younger than 25 years old. This rule identifies them as eligible based on age alone, regardless of location or tourism type.

Tourist c(?t) , tourist_age dp(?t,?age) , lessThan(?) -> has discount coupon dp(?t,"true"^^boolean)

Legend back to ToC

c: Classes
op: Object Properties
dp: Data Properties
ni: Named Individuals
